verbose_text: It has been reported that H1.2 associates with a stable protein complex that influences p53 activity, and murine H1B (equivalent to human H1.2) interacts with the homeobox protein MSX1 to prevent activation of the MYOD gene, thereby delaying myoblast differentiation, suggestive of gene specific regulatory effects.
